  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How can I stop Outlook from synchronising folders automatically?",
  "response": "To stop Outlook from automatically synchronizing folders, you'll need to adjust the settings within the application. Here's a step-by-step guide to help you disable automatic folder synchronization:\n\n1. Open Outlook and go to \"File\" > \"Options.\"\n\n2. In the Outlook Options window, select \"Advanced\" from the left-hand menu.\n\n3. Scroll down to the \"Send and receive\" section and click on the \"Send/Receive\" button.\n\n4. In the Send/Receive Groups window, select the group you want to modify (usually \"All Accounts\").\n\n5. Uncheck the box that says \"Schedule an automatic send/receive every [X] minutes.\"\n\n6. Click \"Close\" to save your changes and then click \"OK\" to exit the Outlook Options window.\n\nBy following these steps, Outlook will no longer automatically synchronize your folders. However, keep in mind that you'll need to manually initiate synchronization when you want to send or receive new emails.\n\nIf you want to synchronize your folders manually, you can do so by clicking on the \"Send/Receive\" button in the main Outlook window or by pressing F9 on your keyboard.\n\nRemember that disabling automatic synchronization might cause delays in receiving new emails or updates to your folders. If you're experiencing issues with Outlook's performance or battery life, you might want to consider increasing the synchronization interval instead of completely disabling it.",
